Ann Shoemaker https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ann_Shoemaker 0 Ann Shoemaker (January 10, 1891 in Brooklyn, New York – September 18, 1978 in Los Angeles, California) was an American actress who appeared in 70 films and TV movies between 1928 and 1976. She portrayed Sara Roosevelt, mother of Franklin D. Roosevelt, in both the stage and film versions of Sunrise at Campobello.She was married to the actor Henry Stephenson; the couple had a daughter.
